<title type="html"><![CDATA[5/8(Sun.) 8 Ways Strength Training Boosts Your Health and Fitness/ How to be more Assertive in Life (Host: Joanne)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=615&amp;p=638#p638"><![CDATA[
5/8(Sun.) 8 Ways Strength Training Boosts Your Health and Fitness/ How to be more Assertive in Life (Host: Joanne)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:35 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:35-9:00 pm Debate<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br />Session 1: 8 Ways Strength Training Boosts Your Health and Fitness<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.everydayhealth.com/fitness/add-strength-training-to-your-workout.aspx">https://www.everydayhealth.com/fitness/ ... rkout.aspx</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion:<br />1.What kind of exercises do you do on a regular basis? What benefits you can get from them?<br /><br />2.Do you know that strength training (weight or resistance training) benefit the heart, improve balance, strengthen bones and muscle, and help you lose or maintain weight ?<br /><br /><br />3.At around age 30 we start losing as much as 3 to 5% of lean muscle mass per decade, what will happen if we do nothing to preserve it?<br /><br />4.According to this article, what benefits, physically and mentally, people can get from strength training? <br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Session 2: How to be more Assertive in Life<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/19071">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/19071</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion:<br />1.Do you find it easy or difficult to stay assertive when necessary? i.e. You have no problem or you do have problem to say YES or No to people.<br /><br />2.Can you share your personal experiences when you have to be assertive? Or, you are afraid to be assertive, and why?<br /><br /><br />3.Do you think the 4 tips mentioned in this video will be usefully to be more assertive? Which tip is the important one? Why?<br /><br />4.Other than the suggestions provided by the author, do you have any other ideas to be assertive if you think this is one of the important personal skills.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46353">Ellen Lu</a> — Thu May 05, 2022 9:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
